(9, 'Privacy Policy', 'privacy-policy', '<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>\r\n        \r\n            <div class=\"col-xxl-12 col-xl-12 col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-12 privacy-sec-text\">\r\n                <p>At Clark and Sons, Inc., your privacy is not just a policy—it\'s a responsibility. This Privacy Policy (referred to as “Policy”) outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you visit our website.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <p>This Policy strictly applies to data and information gathered directly from your interaction with this website. Any earlier activity on our Site may have been governed by previous versions of this Policy.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <p>We reserve the right to use your information for new or evolving purposes. If there are major updates to our data use practices, we will revise this Policy and update you appropriately to ensure transparency and trust.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <p>In cases where your personally identifiable information is held, and we plan to use it in new ways, we’ll seek your approval before doing so.</p>\r\n                \r\n\r\n                <h2>Keeping You Informed: Policy Updates</h2>\r\n                <p>We are committed to aligning our privacy practices with current regulations and industry standards. If we modify this Policy, a revised date will appear, and changes will take effect immediately.</p>\r\n\r\n                <p>Significant changes will be clearly communicated—either directly on our Site or by contacting you. We encourage visitors to review this Policy periodically to stay updated on how we manage and secure personal data.</p>\r\n               \r\n\r\n                <h2>Data We Gather from Your Visit</h2>\r\n                <p>The nature of the information we collect is directly influenced by how you use our Site. We may collect details such as your name, address, contact number, and email if you provide them while interacting with us (“Personal Information”). This may occur through web forms, live chat, or service requests.</p>\r\n\r\n                <p>Participation in such activities is completely voluntary—you control the information you share.</p>\r\n                \r\n                <p>We also automatically collect usage data to improve your browsing experience and ensure our Site runs efficiently. This includes IP addresses, browser type, operating system, access time, visited pages, referral URLs, and on-site behavior metrics.</p>\r\n\r\n                <p>To enhance this tracking, we may use cookies, beacons, or similar tools that allow us to understand how repeat visitors interact with our Site and personalize future visits.</p>\r\n\r\n                <p>Cookies are small files stored on your device to help us recognize returning users. You can delete or disable cookies in your browser settings at any time.</p>\r\n\r\n                <h2>Respecting Do Not Track (DNT) Preferences</h2>\r\n                <p>Your privacy preferences matter. While some browsers support a “Do Not Track” (DNT) signal, there’s currently no standardized method to interpret or enforce these signals.</p>\r\n                <p>Therefore, we do not currently respond to DNT signals. Should future regulations mandate this, we will update this Policy accordingly and notify you of those changes.</p>\r\n\r\n                <h2>Using Analytics to Improve Your Experience</h2>\r\n                <p>We use analytical tools like Google Analytics to understand visitor trends, optimize performance, and improve user experience. These tools may collect data like your IP address, referral source, device type, and user behavior on the Site.</p>\r\n                <p>This data is aggregated and does not personally identify users. Google’s own Privacy Policy and Terms govern the use of any information collected through Google Analytics.</p>\r\n\r\n                <h2>Advertising and Remarketing Tools</h2>\r\n                <p>To provide personalized ads and better experiences, we work with third-party advertising partners who may place cookies on your device during your visit. These cookies allow us to display ads based on your interactions with our Site when you browse elsewhere.</p>\r\n                <p>Our advertising partners do not collect personal identifiers like names, email addresses, or phone numbers.</p>\r\n\r\n                <h2>Our Policy on Minors</h2>\r\n                <p>Clark and Sons, Inc. does not knowingly collect or solicit information from children under 13 years of age. Our services and content are intended for use by adults only.</p>\r\n\r\n                <h2>Secure Payment Information</h2>\r\n                <p>If you make a purchase through our Site, we may collect details such as your payment card number and its corresponding security code to process the transaction.</p>\r\n                <p>All payment data is handled securely and in compliance with industry standards.</p>\r\n\r\n                <h2>Use of Google Maps API</h2>\r\n                <p>To assist with location-based services, we may use Google Maps Platform APIs, which are subject to Google’s Terms of Service. You can view their policy at: <a class=\"in-link\" href=\"https://policies.google.com/privacy\">https://policies.google.com/privacy.</a></p>\r\n                <p>In some cases, we may cache your GPS location for functionality. You may revoke consent by contacting us through the methods provided below.</p>\r\n\r\n                <h2>Information Retention Guidelines</h2>\r\n                <p>We only keep your data for as long as necessary for the business purposes outlined in this Policy or as required by law. Once your data is no longer necessary, we will either delete it, anonymize it, or securely store it to prevent further use.</p>\r\n                <p>If you’ve created an account, we’ll retain your data only while the account is active or as needed for legal, fraud prevention, or system security reasons.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <h2>Email Marketing Opt-Out</h2>\r\n                <p>You can opt out of promotional emails by clicking the “unsubscribe” link in our messages or contacting us directly.</p>\r\n                <p>Even if you unsubscribe from marketing communications, you may still receive emails related to your account, service requests, or security notifications.</p>\r\n\r\n                <h2>Account Information</h2>\r\n                <p>To review, update, or delete your account data, reach out to us using the contact information below. We will respond within 30 days and ensure your rights are respected.</p>\r\n                <p>Once you request an account closure, we will deactivate or delete your data, though certain data may be retained to comply with legal requirements or resolve disputes.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <h2>Contacting Us About This Notice</h2>\r\n                <p>If you have questions, requests, or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please reach out to our Data Protection team using the contact details below.</p>\r\n\r\n                \r\n                <h4 class=\"adr\">Mailing Address:</h4>\r\n                <h4 class=\"inc\">Clark and Sons, Inc.</h4>\r\n                <p> Attn: (Data Protection Officer Contact) <br>314 E Ayre Street <br>Newport, DE 19804 <br>United States</p>\r\n               <p><b>Phone: </b><a class=\"txt\" href=\"tel:+3029987552\">(302) 998-7552</a></p>\r\n               <p><b>Email: </b><a class=\"txt\" href=\"mailto:sales@clarkandsonsdoors.com\">sales@clarkandsonsdoors.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n            </div>', '2025-12-26 07:56:09', '5', NULL, 'Public', NULL, 'Published', '0', '0', NULL, '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Privacy Policy', NULL, 'Your privacy matters to us. Review our Privacy Policy to understand how we protect your information. Contact us today for any questions or assistance.', 'on', NULL, 5, 5, 5, '2025-12-26 06:21:50', '2025-12-26 07:56:09', NULL),
