(6, 'articles', '20', '{\"id\":20,\"title\":\"Everything You Need to Know About Hollow Metal Doors: 2026 Buyer\\u2019s Guide\",\"slug\":\"hollow-metal-doors-buyer-guide-2026\",\"short_description\":\"<p>\\r\\nWhile many homeowners choose wood or fiberglass doors, hollow metal doors are increasingly preferred for their strength, energy efficiency, and low maintenance. <\\/p>\",\"content\":\"<p>\\r\\nWhile many homeowners choose wood or fiberglass doors, hollow metal doors are increasingly preferred for their strength, energy efficiency, and low maintenance. Built to withstand harsh conditions and provide enhanced security, these doors are no longer limited to commercial buildings.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nToday, hollow metal doors are becoming a smart choice for modern homes, especially for exterior entries, garage access, and basement doors where durability and performance matter most.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nThis guide explains how\\r\\n<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/clarkandsonsdoors.com\\/commercial\\/hollow-metal-doors\\/\\\">\\r\\n  hollow metal doors\\r\\n<\\/a>\\r\\nare made and the practical benefits they offer for residential use.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  What Are Hollow Metal Doors?\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nHollow metal doors are constructed from steel or similar metal materials with a reinforced internal core. They typically consist of two steel outer sheets with a supportive core in between, adding strength, insulation, and stability.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nThe term \\u201chollow\\u201d means the door is not solid steel throughout. This design reduces weight and cost while maintaining excellent durability and performance.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nAlthough commonly used in offices, schools, and hospitals, hollow metal doors are now widely installed in homes for exterior doors, garage entry points, and basement access due to their long service life.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Features and Benefits of Hollow Metal Doors\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nHollow metal doors combine strength, durability, and versatility, making them suitable for both\\r\\n<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/clarkandsonsdoors.com\\/residential\\/\\\">\\r\\n  residential\\r\\n<\\/a>\\r\\nand\\r\\n<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/clarkandsonsdoors.com\\/commercial\\/\\\">\\r\\n  commercial\\r\\n<\\/a>\\r\\napplications.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Durable Steel Construction\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nHollow metal doors are made from heavy-duty steel, making them resistant to dents, warping, and cracking. Unlike wood, which can shrink, expand, or split over time, steel doors maintain their shape even with heavy use and extreme weather conditions.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nThis durability reduces long-term repair and replacement costs, making hollow metal doors a practical investment for homeowners seeking long-lasting performance.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Core Materials and Insulation Options\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nThe internal core of a hollow metal door plays a critical role in strength and energy efficiency. Common core options include:\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Honeycomb Core:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Kraft paper arranged in a honeycomb pattern provides structural strength while keeping the door lightweight. Ideal for interior doors where insulation is less critical.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Polystyrene Insulation:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Offers moderate thermal performance and is suitable for exterior doors, helping reduce heat loss in winter and maintain cooler interiors in summer.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Polyurethane Foam:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Provides superior insulation with higher R-values, making it ideal for climates with extreme temperatures and improving overall energy efficiency.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Weather Resistance\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nHollow metal doors are finished with rust-resistant coatings such as powder coating, protecting them from moisture, UV exposure, and corrosion.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"363\\\" data-end=\\\"461\\\" data-is-last-node=\\\"\\\" data-is-only-node=\\\"\\\">\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nUnlike wood doors, they do not swell, rot, or warp, making them especially suitable for humid, rainy, or coastal environments with minimal maintenance requirements\\u2014and Clark &amp; Sons Doors is a trusted <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/clarkandsonsdoors.com\\/\\\">garage door company<\\/a> to help you choose and install the right solution.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Fire Resistance and Safety Features\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nMany hollow metal doors are fire-rated and tested to withstand heat for specific periods. These doors act as barriers that slow the spread of fire, providing valuable additional time during emergencies.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nFire-rated hollow metal doors also help meet local building codes, making them a reliable option for safety-focused homeowners.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Customization Options\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nHollow metal doors offer a wide range of design flexibility. They can be flush or panel-style, fitted with vision panels for natural light, or louvered for ventilation in certain applications.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nAvailable in multiple colors, textures, and powder-coated finishes, hollow metal doors can complement virtually any architectural style without sacrificing strength.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Hollow Metal Doors vs. Other Door Types\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Hollow Metal vs. Wood\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nWood doors require frequent maintenance and are prone to warping, cracking, and insect damage. Hollow metal doors offer greater durability and require significantly less upkeep.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Hollow Metal vs. Solid Metal\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nSolid metal doors are heavier and more expensive. Hollow metal doors provide comparable strength while remaining lighter and offering added benefits such as insulation.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Hollow Metal vs. Fiberglass\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nFiberglass doors can mimic the appearance of wood but offer less impact resistance and security compared to hollow metal doors, especially in exterior or high-risk areas.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Installation of Hollow Metal Doors\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nFor maximum performance, hollow metal doors should be professionally insulated and installed. Proper installation ensures the core material is fitted correctly without gaps or compression that could reduce energy efficiency.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nProfessional installation also ensures the door seals tightly against the frame, preventing drafts, moisture infiltration, and heat loss. The team at Clark &amp; Sons Doors provides expert installation and insulation services to ensure optimal performance and durability.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Frequently Asked Questions\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  What is the lifespan of hollow metal doors?\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nWith proper installation and basic maintenance, hollow metal doors typically last 30 years or more.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Can hollow metal doors be painted?\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nYes. Hollow metal doors can be factory-finished or repainted using appropriate coatings designed for metal surfaces.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  How do I maintain a hollow metal door?\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nMaintenance is simple. Clean the door periodically with mild soap and water, lubricate hardware as needed, and schedule regular professional servicing.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Conclusion\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nHollow metal doors offer an ideal combination of durability, security, energy efficiency, and low maintenance. For homeowners seeking long-term performance and protection, they are a practical and cost-effective choice.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Ready to Upgrade Your Home\\u2019s Doors?\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nContact\\r\\n<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.google.com\\/maps?cid=8195650903324477361\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">\\r\\n  Clark &amp; Sons Doors\\r\\n<\\/a>\\r\\ntoday or call\\r\\n<strong>\\r\\n  <a href=\\\"tel:+18004793667\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">\\r\\n    (800) 479-3667\\r\\n  <\\/a>\\r\\n<\\/strong>\\r\\nto schedule your consultation and find the right hollow metal door for your home.\\r\\n<\\/p>\",\"category_id\":\"9\",\"tag_id\":\"3\",\"published_at\":\"2026-01-10\",\"is_featured\":\"1\",\"image\":\"2866\",\"author\":\"10\",\"visibility\":\"Public\",\"password\":null,\"meta_title\":\"Hollow Metal Doors Buyer Guide 2026 - Clark & Sons\",\"meta_keyword\":null,\"meta_description\":\"Hollow metal doors offer durability, security, fire resistance, and energy efficiency for modern homes and buildings. Learn how to choose the right door.\",\"page_index\":\"on\",\"canonical_url\":null,\"format\":\"Standard\",\"status\":null,\"publish_status\":\"Draft\",\"created_by\":10,\"updated_by\":10,\"deleted_by\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026\\/02\\/18\",\"updated_at\":\"2026\\/02\\/18\",\"deleted_at\":null}', 10, 10, '2026-02-18 16:12:51', '2026-02-18 16:12:51', NULL),
