ile remaining lighter and offering added benefits such as insulation.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Hollow Metal vs. Fiberglass\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nFiberglass doors can mimic the appearance of wood but offer less impact resistance and security compared to hollow metal doors, especially in exterior or high-risk areas.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Installation of Hollow Metal Doors\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nFor maximum performance, hollow metal doors should be professionally insulated and installed. Proper installation ensures the core material is fitted correctly without gaps or compression that could reduce energy efficiency.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nProfessional installation also ensures the door seals tightly against the frame, preventing drafts, moisture infiltration, and heat loss. The team at Clark &amp; Sons Doors provides expert installation and insulation services to ensure optimal performance and durability.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Frequently Asked Questions\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  What is the lifespan of hollow metal doors?\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nWith proper installation and basic maintenance, hollow metal doors typically last 30 years or more.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Can hollow metal doors be painted?\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nYes. Hollow metal doors can be factory-finished or repainted using appropriate coatings designed for metal surfaces.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  How do I maintain a hollow metal door?\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nMaintenance is simple. Clean the door periodically with mild soap and water, lubricate hardware as needed, and schedule regular professional servicing.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Conclusion\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nHollow metal doors offer an ideal combination of durability, security, energy efficiency, and low maintenance. For homeowners seeking long-term performance and protection, they are a practical and cost-effective choice.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Ready to Upgrade Your Home\\u2019s Doors?\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nContact\\r\\n<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.google.com\\/maps?cid=8195650903324477361\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">\\r\\n  Clark &amp; Sons Doors\\r\\n<\\/a>\\r\\ntoday or call\\r\\n<strong>\\r\\n  <a href=\\\"tel:+18004793667\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">\\r\\n    (800) 479-3667\\r\\n  <\\/a>\\r\\n<\\/strong>\\r\\nto schedule your consultation and find the right hollow metal door for your home.\\r\\n<\\/p>\",\"category_id\":\"9\",\"tag_id\":\"3\",\"published_at\":\"2026-01-10\",\"is_featured\":\"0\",\"image\":\"2866\",\"author\":\"10\",\"visibility\":\"Public\",\"password\":null,\"meta_title\":\"Hollow Metal Doors Buyer Guide 2026 - Clark & Sons\",\"meta_keyword\":null,\"meta_description\":\"Hollow metal doors offer durability, security, fire resistance, and energy efficiency for modern homes and buildings. Learn how to choose the right door.\",\"page_index\":\"on\",\"canonical_url\":null,\"format\":\"Standard\",\"status\":null,\"publish_status\":\"Draft\",\"created_by\":10,\"updated_by\":10,\"deleted_by\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026\\/02\\/18\",\"updated_at\":\"2026\\/02\\/18\",\"deleted_at\":null}', 10, 10, '2026-02-19 11:38:16', '2026-02-19 11:38:16', NULL),
(8, 'articles', '19', '{\"id\":19,\"title\":\"When to Repair vs. Replace Your Garage Door: A Cost-Benefit Analysis\",\"slug\":\"garage-door-repair-vs-replacement-guide\",\"short_description\":\"<p>\\r\\nYour garage door is one of the most used features of your home, so when it starts showing signs of wear and tear, it\\u2019s not something you can ignore.\\r\\n<\\/p>\",\"content\":\"<p>\\r\\nYour garage door is one of the most used features of your home, so when it starts showing signs of wear and tear, it\\u2019s not something you can ignore. Many homeowners face the question: should you repair or replace your garage door?\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nWhile a repair might seem easier, sometimes replacing the door is a better long-term investment. Knowing when to repair vs. replace your garage door will save you time, money, and stress.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nThis guide breaks down common issues and weighs the benefits of each option to help you make the best choice.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  When to Repair Your Garage Door\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nIn many cases, a repair is all your garage door needs to get back to working smoothly. Here are a few signs that indicate a repair might be the best option:\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Cosmetic Damage That Doesn\\u2019t Affect Functionality\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nVisible wear like scratches, small dents, or faded paint doesn\\u2019t always mean you need a new door. If your door operates smoothly but looks dated, a few surface-level fixes can save you money while restoring its appearance.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nSimple updates such as applying a fresh coat of paint, replacing worn decorative hardware, or installing new weatherstripping can refresh your home\\u2019s curb appeal without the expense of a full replacement.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Worn-Out Parts\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nSprings, rollers, and cables endure constant strain during every cycle and wear out over time. If your door is becoming increasingly difficult to open or close, this may simply be a sign that a part needs replacement.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nReplacing specific components like springs or rollers is a cost-effective way to extend the life of your garage door. These repairs are typically affordable and straightforward, often completed in a single visit by our professional technicians.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Minor Mechanical Problems\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nIf your\\r\\n<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/clarkandsonsdoors.com\\/residential\\/openers\\/\\\">\\r\\n  garage door opener\\r\\n<\\/a>\\r\\nstops functioning properly, the entire system rarely needs replacing. Sensor misalignments, worn-out remotes, or minor motor issues are often the cause, and they can be resolved with a simple repair.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nOur technicians can quickly diagnose the problem to replace or repair only the necessary parts.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  When to Replace Your Garage Door and Benefits\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nWhile some issues can be repaired, there are cases where replacing your entire garage door is the better choice. Here are key signs that indicate replacement is necessary:\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  The Door is Over 15 Years Old\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nIf your garage door is over 15 years old and breaks down frequently, replacement is likely the best move. Parts are harder to source, and labor for repairs can be costly.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nModern doors offer performance that older models cannot match. They are better insulated, reducing thermal loss by up to 20%, and feature updated safety sensors, quieter operation, and superior durability.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Extensive Damage to Panels or Door Structure\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nSevere damage from storms or accidents often means a door is beyond repair. Deeply dented panels, broken sections, or visible rust compromise structural integrity and safety.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nWhile some doors allow individual panel replacements, widespread damage makes a full replacement the more economical choice. A new door restores appearance and ensures total security.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Higher Energy Bills\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nUninsulated garage doors act as major energy leaks, allowing heat to escape in winter and cool air in summer. This forces your HVAC system to work harder, increasing utility bills.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nUpgrading to a modern, insulated model improves efficiency. High-performance materials like polyurethane foam create a thermal buffer that can reduce annual energy costs by up to 20%.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Cost of Repairs Exceeds Replacement\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nIf you repair your garage door multiple times a year, costs likely approach the price of a full replacement. Repeated service calls on an aging system are often temporary fixes rather than permanent solutions.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nChoosing a new\\r\\n<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/clarkandsonsdoors.com\\/\\\">\\r\\n  garage door\\r\\n<\\/a>\\r\\noffers more than reliable performance; it provides a financial safety net. Most modern doors come with manufacturer warranties that protect against unexpected expenses.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Your Door No Longer Matches Your Home\\u2019s Style\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nSometimes the decision is purely aesthetic. If your garage door looks dated or no longer complements your home\\u2019s architecture, a new installation is the fastest way to modernize your exterior.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nWith a wide range of colors, textures, and contemporary materials, you can transform your garage into a high-end design feature that makes your property stand out.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  So, Repair or Replace?\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nLet the experts help. Our professional technicians will assess your door\\u2019s condition and recommend whether a repair or a full replacement provides the most long-term value.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  FAQs\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Can I install a new garage door on an existing track?\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nYes, a new garage door can be installed on old tracks if it is compatible with the existing system. However, ensure the new door\\u2019s weight and thickness do not exceed the track\'s capacity. Our technicians can determine if your current track is safe or needs replacement.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Does homeowners\\u2019 insurance cover garage door replacement?\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nHomeowners\' insurance typically covers garage door replacement for events like storms, fire, or vandalism. Damage from general wear and tear or poor maintenance is usually not covered. Review your policy or consult your provider to confirm coverage.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Conclusion\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nKnowing when to repair or replace your garage door is key to maintaining your home\\u2019s long-term functionality. Minor repairs address cosmetic wear or individual parts, while replacement is smarter for aging, damaged, or increasingly expensive systems.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Not Sure Whether to Repair or Replace?\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nContact\\r\\n<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.google.com\\/maps?cid=8195650903324477361\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">\\r\\n  Clark &amp; Sons Doors\\r\\n<\\/a>\\r\\ntoday or call\\r\\n<strong>\\r\\n  <a href=\\\"tel:+18004793667\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">\\r\\n    (800) 479-3667\\r\\n  <\\/a>\\r\\n<\\/strong>\\r\\nto help you choose the best option for your home with expert installation and service.\\r\\n<\\/p>\",\"category_id\":\"8\",\"tag_id\":\"3\",\"published_at\":\"2025-12-20\",\"is_featured\":\"0\",\"image\":\"2865\",\"author\":\"10\",\"visibility\":\"Public\",\"password\":null,\"meta_title\":\"Garage Door Repair vs Replacement Guide - Clark and Sons\",\"meta_keyword\":null,\"meta_description\":\"Understanding when to repair or replace your garage door can save money, boost safety, and improve efficiency. Learn how to pick the best option today.\",\"page_index\":\"on\",\"canonical_url\":null,\"format\":\"Standard\",\"status\":null,\"publish_status\":\"Draft\",\"created_by\":10,\"updated_by\":10,\"deleted_by\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026\\/02\\/18\",\"updated_at\":\"2026\\/02\\/18\",\"deleted_at\":null}', 10, 10, '2026-02-19 11:46:00', '2026-02-19 11:46:00', NULL),
(9, 'articles', '21', '{\"id\":21,\"title\":\"Safe Loading and Unloading? Dock Doors for the Loading Dock: 2026 Expert Guide\",\"slug\":\"safe-loading-and-unloading-dock-doors-2026\",\"short_description\":\"<p>\\r\\nManaging a warehouse or distribution center involves constant traffic, heavy trucks, and fast-moving forklifts.  <\\/p>\",\"content\":\"<p>\\r\\nManaging a warehouse or distribution center involves constant traffic, heavy trucks, and fast-moving forklifts. Without the right equipment, the loading dock can become a high-risk area where injuries occur, products are damaged, and energy costs rise.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nOne of the most critical yet often overlooked components of a warehouse is the loading dock, where many operational hazards arise. This is where dock doors play a vital role in maintaining safety, efficiency, and control.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nIn this guide, we break down everything you need to know about safe loading and unloading with <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/clarkandsonsdoors.com\\/commercial\\/loading-dock-doors\\/\\\">dock doors<\\/a> and how they improve loading dock performance.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  What Are Dock Doors and Why Do They Matter?\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nDock doors are heavy-duty industrial doors installed at warehouse loading bays. Unlike standard doors, they are engineered to withstand repeated impacts from forklifts and trucks, extreme weather conditions, and continuous daily use.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nWithout proper dock doors, facilities face increased accident risks, product damage, energy loss, and operational delays that disrupt workflow and increase costs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  The Benefits of Dock Doors for Safe Loading and Unloading\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Improved Safety\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nThe right dock doors help protect workers from common loading dock hazards such as collisions, falls, and crush injuries. Modern dock doors are designed with advanced safety features, including:\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Impact-Resistant Construction:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Heavy-duty steel or aluminum doors withstand accidental impacts from forklifts and machinery while maintaining structural integrity.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Safety Sensors and Auto-Stop Mechanisms:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Integrated sensors detect obstacles and automatically stop or reverse the door\\u2019s movement to prevent injuries and equipment damage.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Visibility Windows:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Vision panels and full-vision sectional doors improve visibility, allowing better communication between operators and reducing accident risks.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Improved Efficiency\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nIn high-volume warehouses, every second matters. Proper dock doors keep loading and unloading fast, predictable, and coordinated.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      High-Speed Operation:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Rapid-opening doors can reduce truck dwell time by 50\\u201370%, improving throughput and turnaround times.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Quick Access:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Fast-opening doors eliminate delays for forklifts and trucks, preventing operational bottlenecks.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Automation Integration:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Dock doors can integrate with warehouse management systems, ensuring doors operate only when trucks are correctly positioned.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Energy Efficiency\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nLoading docks are a major source of energy loss. Open or poorly sealed dock doors allow conditioned air to escape, driving up heating and cooling costs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Insulated Doors:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Multi-layer steel or aluminum doors with polyurethane cores help maintain internal temperatures and reduce energy costs by 20\\u201330%.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Weather Seals:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Tight seals prevent drafts, moisture, dust, rain, and snow from entering the warehouse.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Dock Shelters:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Inflatable or foam dock shelters reduce temperature exchange during loading and unloading.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Improved Security\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nDock doors are the first line of defense against theft and unauthorized access. They help control who operates the doors and protect both inventory and personnel.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Access Control:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Integration with keypads, RFID cards, or biometric systems ensures only authorized personnel can operate dock doors.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Durable Construction:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Heavy-duty materials and tight sealing make forced entry more difficult.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Cost Savings\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nHigh-quality dock doors reduce long-term operating costs through improved efficiency, durability, and product protection.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Energy Savings:\\r\\n    <\\/strong><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/clarkandsonsdoors.com\\/residential\\/polyurethane-insulated-garage-doors\\/\\\">\\r\\n    Insulated doors<\\/a> reduce HVAC load and can lower energy costs by thousands of dollars annually.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Durable Materials:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Heavy-gauge steel doors resist forklift and truck damage, with lifespans exceeding 20 years when properly maintained.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Reduced Product Loss:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Tight seals and temperature control prevent spoilage, contamination, and product damage.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Environmental Control\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nMaintaining a stable warehouse environment is critical, especially for temperature-sensitive products.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Temperature Stability:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Insulated doors prevent rapid temperature changes that affect perishable goods or electronics.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Air Quality:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Seals reduce dust, debris, and pests, protecting inventory and improving worker safety.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Noise Reduction:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Heavy-duty dock doors minimize external noise, improving communication inside the facility.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Types of Dock Doors\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nChoosing the right dock door depends on traffic levels, operational demands, and product requirements. Common options include:\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Sectional Overhead Doors\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nSectional overhead <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/clarkandsonsdoors.com\\/\\\">garage doors<\\/a> are made of hinged panels that open vertically, making them ideal for facilities with limited front clearance. They can be insulated for temperature control and are commonly used in general-purpose warehouses.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Full Vision Sectional Doors\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nThese doors feature large glass or polycarbonate panels that enhance visibility and allow natural light into the workspace. Full vision doors improve safety and are ideal for facilities requiring clear line-of-sight awareness.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  High-Speed Doors\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nHigh-speed dock doors open and close rapidly to handle high-traffic areas. They minimize energy loss, maintain workflow efficiency, and are commonly used in cold storage and fast-paced distribution centers.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Essential Dock Door Accessories\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nDock doors alone are not enough to ensure optimal safety and performance. Essential accessories include:\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Dock Levelers:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Bridge the gap between truck beds and loading docks for safer forklift operation.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Dock Shelters:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Create a tight seal between the trailer and dock to reduce energy loss and weather exposure.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Dock Bumpers:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Protect both trucks and buildings from impact damage.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    <strong>\\r\\n      Dock Lights:\\r\\n    <\\/strong>\\r\\n    Improve visibility during early morning or nighttime operations.\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Choosing the Right Dock Door for Your Facility\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nSelecting the best dock door requires careful consideration of several factors:\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    Traffic volume and daily usage\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    Temperature control requirements\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    Security needs\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    Door size and clearance\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n  <li>\\r\\n    Budget and long-term operating costs\\r\\n  <\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Why Professional Installation Is Important\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nProfessional installation ensures dock doors operate safely, meet electrical and safety codes, and deliver long-term performance. Improper installation can lead to malfunctions, energy loss, and safety risks.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nThe team at Clark &amp; Sons Doors provides expert dock door installation services designed to enhance safety, efficiency, and durability for your loading dock.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Conclusion\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nInvesting in high-quality dock doors is essential for creating a safer, more efficient, and cost-effective loading dock. The right dock doors protect workers, improve workflow, and significantly reduce energy costs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Ready to Improve Your Loading Dock?\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nContact\\r\\n<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.google.com\\/maps?cid=8195650903324477361\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">\\r\\n  Clark &amp; Sons Doors\\r\\n<\\/a>\\r\\ntoday for a free consultation and let our experts help you design a safer, more efficient loading dock for your facility.\\r\\n<\\/p>\",\"category_id\":\"9\",\"tag_id\":\"3\",\"published_at\":\"2026-01-20\",\"is_featured\":\"0\",\"image\":\"2867\",\"author\":\"10\",\"visibility\":\"Public\",\"password\":null,\"meta_title\":\"Safe Loading and Unloading Dock Doors 2026 - Clark & Sons\",\"meta_keyword\":null,\"meta_description\":\"Safe loading and unloading starts with the right dock doors. Improve warehouse safety, efficiency, energy control, and security with expert guidance for 2026.\",\"page_index\":\"on\",\"canonical_url\":null,\"format\":\"Standard\",\"status\":null,\"publish_status\":\"Draft\",\"created_by\":10,\"updated_by\":10,\"deleted_by\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026\\/02\\/18\",\"updated_at\":\"2026\\/02\\/18\",\"deleted_at\":null}', 10, 10, '2026-02-19 11:51:38', '2026-02-19 11:51:38', NULL),
(10, 'articles', '18', '{\"id\":18,\"title\":\"Garage Door Trends 2026: Design, Materials & Smart Features\",\"slug\":\"modern-garage-door-trends-2026\",\"short_description\":\"<p>\\r\\nGarage doors have come a long way from being just functional openings.  <\\/p>\",\"content\":\"<p>\\r\\nGarage doors have come a long way from being just functional openings. In 2026, they are set to become central to your home\'s design, security, and energy efficiency. No longer limited to basic panels and automatic openers, modern garage doors enhance convenience and overall home functionality.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nIn this article, the Clark &amp; Sons team takes you through the biggest garage door trends for 2026, highlighting the designs, materials, and smart features that redefine what a garage door can do.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Design Trends for Garage Doors in 2026\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nHere\\u2019s a peek at the design trends shaping the garage doors of 2026:\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Sleek, Minimalist Designs\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nOne of the most dominant trends in garage door design for 2026 is minimalism. Homeowners are opting for clean lines, smooth surfaces, and understated elegance. Forget about intricate paneling and over-the-top decoration; the future of garage doors is all about simplicity and sophistication.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/clarkandsonsdoors.com\\/\\\">\\r\\n  Modern garage doors\\r\\n<\\/a>\\r\\nwill feature large, flat panels with little to no visible hardware, creating a seamless look that aligns perfectly with contemporary home architecture.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Glass and Aluminum Combinations\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nGlass and aluminum create a sleek, industrial look for homeowners who want their garage door to make a bold statement. These doors bring natural light into the garage, making the space feel larger and more inviting.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nCustomizable glass options, including clear, frosted, or tinted finishes, allow you to balance light with privacy according to your needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Bold Colors and Custom Finishes\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nHomeowners in 2026 are embracing bold colors and custom finishes. Matte black, deep blue, and rich wood textures are trending, adding depth and dimension to your home\\u2019s exterior.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nWith plenty of customization options, you can create a garage door that perfectly reflects your personal style.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Materials to Watch in 2026 Garage Doors\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nDurability, sustainability, and aesthetic appeal will all play a role in selecting the best material for your door. Here are the materials set to dominate the market:\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  High-Performance Steel\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nSteel remains a top choice in 2026, but modern doors use high-performance steel that is both lightweight and incredibly durable. These doors resist rust, dents, and fading while offering a wide range of finishes, from textured to glossy.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nBuilt-in insulation options improve energy efficiency by helping regulate your garage\\u2019s temperature, reducing heating and cooling costs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Eco-Friendly Materials\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nSustainability is a growing priority, and eco-friendly materials like reclaimed wood, fiberglass, and composites are becoming popular. Reclaimed wood offers rustic charm while reducing waste, while fiberglass and composites combine durability with low maintenance.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Insulated Garage Doors\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nInsulated garage doors remain a must-have for energy efficiency. Featuring foam or polystyrene cores between layers of material, these doors maintain comfortable indoor temperatures and help lower energy bills.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Garage Door Smart Features in 2026\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Smart Connectivity and Automation\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nWi-Fi-enabled openers and mobile apps put total control in your hands from anywhere in the world. You can monitor and operate your garage door in real time straight from your smartphone.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Voice Control Integration\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nVoice assistants like Amazon Alexa or Google Assistant allow you to operate your door with simple commands, making access effortless even when your hands are full.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Advanced Security Features\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nRolling code technology ensures your garage door access code changes automatically each time it\\u2019s used. Additional features such as motion sensors, camera integration, and biometric authentication enhance security and prevent unauthorized access.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>\\r\\n  Energy Efficiency\\r\\n<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nSmart garage doors not only improve convenience but also help regulate garage temperatures, reducing utility bills and increasing overall energy efficiency.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Sustainability of Garage Doors in 2026\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nSustainable garage door options use recycled materials and eco-friendly manufacturing processes, allowing homeowners to make environmentally conscious choices without sacrificing style or durability.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nMaterials like reclaimed wood, fiberglass, and composites offer superior insulation while positively impacting the planet and lowering long-term utility costs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Conclusion\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nThe garage door trends of 2026 are exciting, functional, and packed with innovation. From sleek minimalist designs and eco-friendly materials to cutting-edge smart features, a modern garage door offers far more than just curb appeal. It is a vital investment in your home\\u2019s security, energy efficiency, and daily convenience.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>\\r\\n  Ready to Upgrade Your Garage Door?\\r\\n<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nContact\\r\\n<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.google.com\\/maps?cid=8195650903324477361\\\">\\r\\n \\r\\n  Clark &amp; Sons Doors\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/a>\\r\\n<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.google.com\\/maps?cid=8195650903324477361\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">\\r\\n<\\/a>\\r\\ntoday or call\\r\\n<strong>\\r\\n  <a href=\\\"tel:+18004793667\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">\\r\\n    (800) 479-3667\\r\\n  <\\/a>\\r\\n<\\/strong>\\r\\nto explore garage door options that combine high-end design with the latest technology and fit your home and budget.\\r\\n<\\/p>\",\"category_id\":\"7\",\"tag_id\":\"3\",\"published_at\":\"2025-12-10\",\"is_featured\":\"0\",\"image\":\"2864\",\"author\":\"10\",\"visibility\":\"Public\",\"password\":null,\"meta_title\":\"Modern Garage Door Trends 2026 \\u2013 Clark & Sons\",\"meta_keyword\":null,\"meta_description\":\"Garage doors in 2026 combine modern minimalist designs, durable materials, energy-efficient insulation, and smart features. Learn the best options today.\",\"page_index\":\"on\",\"canonical_url\":null,\"format\":\"Standard\",\"status\":null,\"publish_status\":\"Draft\",\"created_by\":10,\"updated_by\":10,\"deleted_by\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026\\/02\\/18\",\"updated_at\":\"2026\\/02\\/18\",\"deleted_at\":null}', 10, 10, '2026-02-20 06:53:28', '2026-02-20 06:53:28', NULL);
